Red Widow is an upcoming American drama television series created by Melissa Rosenberg, starring Radha Mitchell and Goran Visnjic. On May 11, 2012, ABC picked up "Red Widow" as a series. Season one will begin on Sunday, March 3, 2013 and will consist of eight episodes. The series is based on a 2010 Dutch drama entitled "Penoza" created by Pieter Bart Korthuis and Diederik van Rooijen.
Overview.
The series stars Radha Mitchell as Marta Walraven, a housewife from Northern California whose husband, a figure in organized crime, was killed. She has to continue his work to protect her family.
